Package scs1_group1.menu

Class AdministratorMenu

Object
Menu
AdministratorMenu
public class AdministratorMenu extends Menu
Menu class to manage various administrative operations in the Hospital Management System. Allows the administrator to manage appointments, staff, medicines, replenishment requests, and alert levels.

    • changeAlertLevel

      private void changeAlertLevel()
      Changes the alert level for a specific medicine. Displays the list of medicines and allows the administrator to update the alert threshold.

    • manageMedicine

      private void manageMedicine()
      Manages the medicines in the system. Allows the administrator to update medicine stock levels.

    • manageReplenishmentRequest

      private void manageReplenishmentRequest()
      Manages the replenishment requests in the system. Allows the administrator to approve or reject requests for replenishing medicine stock.

    • viewAppointment

      public void viewAppointment()
      Displays all the appointments in the system. Provides an overview of appointments including their status and the associated doctor and patient.

    • manageStaff

      private void manageStaff()
      Manages the staff in the hospital. Provides options to add, edit, or delete staff members.

    • addStaff

      private void addStaff()
      Adds a new staff member to the system. Prompts the administrator for staff details including role, ID, name, and other details.

    • getContainerByType

      private void editStaff()
      Edits the details of an existing staff member. Prompts the administrator to enter new values for specific fields.

    • deleteStaff

      private void deleteStaff()
      Deletes a staff member from the system. Removes the staff member identified by their hospital ID.

    • printAllStaff

      private void printAllStaff()
      Displays all the staff in the system. Provides options to filter staff by gender, age, or role.

    • genderFilteredView

      public void genderFilteredView()
      Displays staff filtered by gender. Allows the administrator to view only male or female staff.

    • ageFilteredView

      public void ageFilteredView()
      Displays staff filtered by age range. Allows the administrator to specify a lower and upper limit for age.

    • roleFilterView

      public void roleFilterView()
      Displays staff filtered by role. Allows the administrator to view staff by specific roles such as Doctor, Pharmacist, or Administrator.

    • noFilterView

      public void noFilterView()
      Displays all staff members without any filters.
